"title": "5922: prudence",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5922",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Careful, wise discernment; the avoidance of rash behaviour or speech; the good management of talents and resources and the showing of tact and wisdom in relationships with other people.</p>\n<h2>The link between prudence and wisdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:12\">PRO 8:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:1-Prov1:6\">PRO 1:1–1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of prudence</h2>\n<h3>Discernment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:15\">PRO 14:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:16\">PRO 12:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:8\">PRO 14:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:28-Luke14:32\">LUK 14:28–14:32</a></p>\n<h3>Foresight and caution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:3\">PRO 22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:1-Prov23:3\">PRO 23:1–23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:13\">AMO 5:13</a></p>\n<h3>Wise use of knowledge</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:23\">PRO 12:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:18\">PRO 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:6\">MAT 7:6</a></p>\n<h3>Wise speech</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:23\">PRO 21:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:1\">PSA 39:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:5-Jas3:8\">JAS 3:5–3:8</a></p>\n<h3>A teachable spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:5\">PRO 15:5</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Prudence involves good management of talents and resources</h2>\n<h3>Good management commended</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:6-Prov6:11\">PRO 6:6–6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:33-Gen41:40\">GEN 41:33–41:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:27\">PRO 24:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:30\">MAT 25:14–25:30</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings against unwise financial dealings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:26-Prov22:27\">PRO 22:26–22:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:1-Prov6:5\">PRO 6:1–6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25-Matt5:26\">MAT 5:25–5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of prudent behaviour</h2>\n<h3>In averting disaster</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:14-1Sam25:35\">1SA 25:14–25:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:3-Gen32:21\">GEN 32:3–32:21</a></p>\n<h3>In avoiding persecution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:5-Acts14:7\">ACT 14:5–14:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:14-Matt12:16\">MAT 12:14–12:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:6-Mark3:7\">MRK 3:6–3:7</a> <em>Jesus Christ</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:23-Acts9:25\">ACT 9:23–9:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:29-Acts9:30\">ACT 9:29–9:30</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:17\">ACT 12:17</a> <em>Peter</em></p>\n<h3>Prudence in dealing with other people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:26-Gen26:31\">GEN 26:26–26:31</a> <em>Abimelech makes a treaty with Isaac</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:3-Gen32:21\">GEN 32:3–32:21</a> <em>Jacob prepares to meet Esau</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:1-Neh2:6\">NEH 2:1–2:6</a> <em>Nehemiah petitions Artaxerxes</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:8-Dan1:14\">DAN 1:8–1:14</a> <em>Daniel's diplomacy in avoiding Nebuchanezzar's food</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:10-Dan2:16\">DAN 2:10–2:16</a> <em>Daniel's wisdom and tact in the face of death</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:15-Matt22:22\">MAT 22:15–22:22</a> <em>Jesus Christ's wisdom on the question of paying taxes to Caesar</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:33-Acts5:40\">ACT 5:33–5:40</a> <em>Gamaliel's speech to the Sanhedrin</em></p>",
